# Database Rules

PostgreSQL/PostGIS is the source of truth.

Required patterns:
- Use UUID or stable text IDs consistently per table family.
- Add GiST indexes for geometry columns.
- Add GIN indexes for JSONB and full-text fields that will be queried.
- Add B-tree indexes for source/status/timestamp/assignee/channel columns.
- Store media/raw file binaries in S3/MinIO, never directly in PostgreSQL.
- Treat high-volume append-only tables as partition-ready.

Keep schema changes paired with repository tests and migration tests.
